James Oatway took images of Mozambique national Emmanuel Sithole being stabbed and beaten by four men in Alexandra township near Johannesburg on Saturday . 
  He has spoken out after coming under fire for taking pictures instead of trying to save the victim . 
  Mr Sithole was taken to a medical centre but it was closed because the foreign-born doctor had failed to turn up for his shift . 
  Four South African men have been accused of murder in the attack . 
  Photographer said it was vital for people to see the brutality of anti-immigrant protests . 
 